    "updated_at": "2012-05-19T10:24:32Z",
    "body": "If I understand correctly then the `:` in the new syntax makes the difference between a regular lambda and a last-argument-to-call lambda greater than in the current syntax, i.e:\n\nCurrent syntax: `vec.map({|x| x+1})` vs `vec.map {|x| x+1}`\n\nProposed syntax: `vec.map(|x| {x + 1})` vs `vec.map: |x| {x + 1}`\n\nI therefore suggest that this proposal increases syntactic complexity.\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
